data.title: Bon Iver
data.subtitle: Live in Concert
data.shortDescription: Bon Iver gave an exclusive concert at the Sounds From A Safe Harbour festival in Cork in autumn 2017, along with Irish musician Lisa Hannigan, a choir, and brothers Bryce and Aaron Dessner from The National. He delighted his fans with a mix of new songs and new versions of his previous hits. A unique appearance.

data.title: Akram Khan's XENOS
data.shortDescription: Akram Khan shows the human condition in its beauty and horror with the portrait of an Indian dancer whose body becomes an instrument of war. In this solo piece mixing classical kathak and contemporary dance, the British choreographer is joined onstage by five international musicians.

data.subtitle: Daniel Hope with Hornist Sarah Willis
data.shortDescription: Violinist Daniel Hope invites artists into his home in Berlin for an intimate and impromptu concert. The perfect antidote to this period of lockdown and crisis. This evening he is joined by pianist Christoph Israel and special guest Sarah Willis, horn player with the Berlin Philharmonic.

data.title: Puccini's Tosca
data.subtitle: An Operatic Thriller from Helsinki Opera
data.shortDescription: One moment the singer Floria Tosca is standing on the stage, next moment she is the key figure in a deadly political intrigue sparked by jealousy and the craving for power. Giacomo Puccini’s thriller continues to captivate audiences to this day. Helsinki presents an audacious new production of this classic directed by Christof Loy.

data.title: Hommage to Krzysztof Penderecki
data.shortDescription: Polish composer Krzysztof Penderecki passed away on 29th March 2020. ARTE celebrates this remarkable musical talent with the reprogramming of a gala concert in his honour, recorded at the Wielki Theatre in Warsaw, featuring violinist Anne-Sophie Mutter, double bassist Roman Patkolo and conductor Valery Gergiev.

data.title: ARTE Opera Season 2019-2020
data.shortDescription: 23 opera houses, 14 countries, one season. ARTE Concert presents some exceptional productions including the great classics, new productions and revivals, all filmed on the greatest opera stages in Europe. Every month, new operas are available in six languages. Find all the diversity, creativity and innovation of the world of opera in ARTE Opera Season – exclusively on ARTE Concert.

data.title: Katie Melua
data.subtitle: Performing her Latest Album
data.shortDescription: British singer/songwriter Katie Melua, whose work includes pop, jazz and blues influences, performs her latest album, In Winter, with the Georgian Gori Women's Choir in Berlin.

data.title: Richard Galliano and the Polish National Radio Symphony Orchestra
data.subtitle: Zadymka Festival
data.shortDescription: To celebrate a fifty year career, accordionist Richard Galliano gives a special performance with the Polish National Radio Symphony Orchestra. On the programme: the ‘Aconcagua’ concerto for bandoneon and orchestra by Astor Piazzola and his own composition ‘Madreperla’.

data.title: Sepultura in Concert
data.subtitle: Hellfest Special
data.shortDescription: A special evening with Hellfest Festival at the Maroquinerie in Paris. Legendary Brazilian band Sepultura play tracks from their upcoming album Quadra to celebrate the announcement of the 2020 lineup.

data.title: Yann Tiersen's "All"
data.subtitle: From the Island of Ushant
data.shortDescription: Composer and pianist Yann Tiersen has lived on Ushant, off the West coast of Brittany, for more than fifteen years. He composed his latest album ‘All’ there and this Release Party was also filmed on the starkly beautiful island, mixing Aldo Leopold’s writings on nature and wilderness with Tiersen’s haunting new album.

data.title: Ron Carter  and Richard Galliano
data.subtitle: Two Giants of Contemporary Jazz
data.shortDescription: For a few days in March the Polish city of Katowice becomes the epicentre of the Jazz world as the Zadymka Festival comes to town. Two contemporary jazz giants, accordionist Richard Galliano and double bassist Ron Carter shared the stage for a memorable evening of music.

data.title: Interpol - The Paris Ghost Session
data.subtitle: A Unique Recording
data.shortDescription: In a special session recorded in a vast empty studio in Paris, the perfect accompaniment to the New York band’s moody, dark sound, Interpol give an assured performance.

data.title: Patrick Watson Live at the Paris Olympia
data.shortDescription: Canadian singer-songwriter Patrick Watson’s melancholy sound recalls Nick Drake, Sufjan Stevens, Björk or even the Beatles. His highly persona sixth studio album ‘Wave’, released in October 2019, provides the songs for an emotional performance in a mythic Paris venue, the Olympia. Recorded live February 26, 2020.

data.title: Foals Live
data.subtitle: Everything Not Saved Will Be Lost
data.shortDescription: The Foals are back with not one but two albums, ‘Everything Not Saved Will Be Lost Part 1 & 2’. Discover them both at this special appearance of the Oxford boys at the Gaîté Lyrique in Paris, part of the ARTE Concert Festival.

data.title: Iggy Pop
data.subtitle: ARTE Concert Festival
data.shortDescription: In August 2018, Iggy Pop surprised planet rock with the announcement of a new album in the pipeline. Discover the Godfather of Punk’s latest album, ‘Free’, in this live performance at the Gaîté Lyrique Theatre in Paris, part of the ARTE Concert Festival.

data.title: Beethoven 2020
data.shortDescription: 2020 marks the 250th anniversary of the birth of Ludwig van Beethoven.  ARTE celebrates throughout the year with his best works performed by outstanding musicians past and present.

data.title: Tamino at the Paris Olympia
data.shortDescription: In the mythic Paris venue, Belgian artist Tamino performs tracks from his intimate and melancholy debut album, Amir. Recorded on 19 November 2019.

data.title: Neue Stimmen 2019
data.subtitle: International Singing Competition
data.shortDescription: Ten international artists compete in the final of the Neue Stimmen (new voices) singing competition. All of the finalists are passionate and talented young singers. Accompaniment from the Duisburg Philharmonic Orchestra.

data.title: Festival mondial du Cirque de Demain
data.subtitle: Circus Stars of Tomorrow
data.shortDescription: Every year since 1977 the next generation of circus talent meets in Paris to compete in a prestigious prize ‘le Festival Mondial du Cirque de Demain’ the World Festival of the circus of the future. Be amazed by jugglers, acrobats, clowns and trapeze artists.

data.title: Blanco White at Eurosonic
data.shortDescription: Blanco White's intimate blend of folk is as much influenced by the Villagers or James Vincent McMorrow as Andalusian and Latin American music. Recorded live in Groeningen, the Netherlands.

data.title: Altin Gün
data.subtitle: Dutch-Turkish Rock
data.shortDescription: The golden age of Turkish psychedelic rock is back with Altin Gün, a group of Amsterdam musicians fascinated by Turkey, founded by Jasper Verhulst. Concert recorded live on 16 August at La Route du Rock festival, France.

data.title: Dégage at Cabaret Vert Festival
data.shortDescription: Their name is an aggressive command in French and yet the Gallic foursome’s music is smooth, well-crafted and often delicate. With pleasing electro overtones, could this be French pop’s heir to Air? Recorded live on 22 August at Cabaret Vert Festival.

data.subtitle: From the Helsinki Opera
data.shortDescription: Pippi Longstocking, the superhumanly strong redhead with pigtails and freckles, conquers the world of classical ballet. The Swedish dancer and choreographer Pär Isberg stages Astrid Lindgren’s favourite character from the Villa Villekulla for the Helsinki opera house. The ballet music is the work of Georg Riedel and Stefan Nilsson.

data.title: #UnitedWeStream
data.subtitle: We Bring the Club to You

United We Stream supports those clubs, artists and organisers by livestreaming from the empty club direct to your living room, where you can rave from the comfort and safety of your home. Get ready to join the biggest virtual club in the world!

data.title: Teatro Real
data.subtitle: Madrid
data.shortDescription: The Teatro Real is considered as one of the most important institutions of the Spanish theatre world. It serves as a major national opera as well as one of the most prestigious cultural institutions of Spain. At the Teatro Real, you find opera on an international level.

data.title: Zurich Opera House
data.shortDescription: The Zurich Opera House is the biggest cultural institution in Switzerland and one of the most productive opera houses in Europe with over 300 performances a year, including 12 new productions on the main stage as well as several revivals, concerts and recitals. It also provides a hugely important space for young talent. The opera house was built in 1891 and is a limited company.

data.title: Latvian National Opera
data.subtitle: Riga
data.shortDescription: The Latvian National Opera and Ballet is an internationally competitive arts centre which aims to develop and support the creative process, cultural enrichment and educational functions. The company has operated under numerous authorities and regimes since 1918. It has always staged most influential opera and ballet masterpieces, as well as modern examples of the genre.

data.title: Dutch National Opera
data.shortDescription: Dutch National Opera creates and performs dramatic musical art, focusing on quality, diversity and innovation. This is expressed by taking a fresh approach to the opera classics, rediscovering repertoire that has seldom been performed and creating brand-new operas. Come and be inspired in our theatre, where you will be given a warm welcome.

data.title: Opéra Comique
data.shortDescription: Founded in 1715, the Opéra Comique is one of the oldest cultural institutions in France. Its repertoire is a mix of theatre and opera. It has produced the world’s most often-performed French operatic masterpieces including Carmen, Lakmé, Manon, The Tales of Hoffmann and Pelléas and Mélisande. It was designated as a national theatre in 2005 and has been managed by Olivier Mantei since 2015.

data.title: Semperoper Dresden
data.shortDescription: The Semperoper is considered one of the most beautiful theatres of the world and is renowned for its exceptional acoustics and its astounding artistic quality. The company’s soloist ensemble as well as the Staatskapelle Dresden, the Semperoper ballet and numerous international guests all permanently contribute to it.

data.title: Royal Opera House
data.shortDescription: The Royal Opera, under the direction of Antonio Pappano, is one of the world’s leading opera companies. Based in the iconic Covent Garden theatre, it is renowned both for its outstanding performances of traditional opera and for commissioning new works by today’s leading opera composers, such as Harrison Birtwistle, Mark-Anthony Turnage and Thomas Adès.

data.title: Hamburg State Opera
data.shortDescription: The Hamburg State Opera with General Director Georges Delnon and Kent Nagano, General Music Director and Chief Conductor of the Philharmonic State Orchestra, holds a significant place within the musical scene of the Hanseatic city. The house maintains a delicate balance between carefully selected repertoire pieces and a distinctive passion for contemporary works.

data.title: Staatsoper Unter den Linden
data.shortDescription: The Staatsoper Unter den Linden, founded in 1742, presents a programme of the highest artistic level - from baroque opera to central works of classical, romantic and modern opera, as well as world premieres and developments of experimental forms of music theatre. The historic building in the centre of Berlin has recently undergone an extensive reconstruction.

data.title: Finnish National Opera
data.shortDescription: Finnish National Opera and Ballet is Finland’s national theatre for opera and ballet, offering performances and other events to audiences of all ages. Guest performances, school operas, TV broadcasts and streaming bring FNOB to everyone all over Finland and even the globe. The FNOB is the only professional opera and ballet company in Finland. It traces its history back to 1911.
